            . I am a <rs id="t18290611-224-viclabel1173" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-224-victim1660 t18290611-224-viclabel1173"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18290611-224-crimeloc1174">Brick-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-224-crimeloc1174" type="placeName" value="Brick-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290611-224-crimeloc1174" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-224-off1171 t18290611-224-crimeloc1174"></join>. On the 24th of April I saw the prisoner take this beef from my counter, as I was in the adjoining room to my shop - he threw a handkerchief over it, and ran away with it; I pursued and overtook him - when he saw me, he threw it down and ran away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-224-person1662">
                  JOSEPH 
                  DYSON
               <interp inst="t18290611-224-person1662" type="surname" value="DYSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-224-person1662" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290611-224-person1662" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I stopped the prisoner about threehundred yards from the spot; a young man came up and said he had stolen a piece of beef - I took him back to Mr. Mendy.</p>
               <p>Three witnesses gave the prisoner a good character, and one of them engaged to employ him.</p>
